## Submitting Solutions

Navigate to submit page, then:
```javascript
(function() {
    // Select problem
    var prob = document.querySelector('select[name="submittedProblemIndex"]');
    prob.value = 'A';  // A, B, C, D, E, F...
    prob.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', {bubbles: true}));

    // Select language — always use G++17
    var lang = document.querySelector('select[name="programTypeId"]');
    for (var i = 0; i < lang.options.length; i++) {
        if (lang.options[i].text.indexOf('G++17') >= 0) {
            lang.value = lang.options[i].value;
            break;
        }
    }

    // Paste source code into textarea
    var ta = document.querySelector('textarea[name="source"]')
          || document.getElementById('sourceCodeTextarea');
    ta.value = CODE_STRING;
    ta.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', {bubbles: true}));

    // Submit
    document.querySelector('input[type="submit"]').click();
})()
```

**Language options available:**
- GNU G++17 7.3.0 (value typically `54`)
- GNU G++20 13.2 (64 bit, winlibs)
- GNU G++23 14.2 (64 bit, msys2)

**Always use G++17** per course requirements.

**Important:** Pass source code via `json.dumps(code)` in Python to properly escape quotes and newlines.

## Checking Verdicts

Navigate to My Submissions page (`/my`):
```javascript
